IMPROVED COLORING OPTIONS FOR MESSAGE COMPOSE WINDOW
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

&lt;b&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;i&gt;Account Colors&lt;/i&gt; allows a font color and a background color to be associated with each account or identity. The colors for an account are the same as the colors for its default identity. Colors can be defined for a maximum of 60 identities.  The colors and other settings can be changed in the &lt;i&gt;Account Colors Options&lt;/i&gt; dialog.

&lt;b&gt;USER REFERENCE&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Accessing Account Colors Options&lt;/b&gt;

The &lt;i&gt;Options Dialog&lt;/i&gt; can be accessed in two ways:
    • either by selecting &lt;i&gt;Tools&lt;/i&gt; | &lt;i&gt;Account Colors Options...&lt;/i&gt; on the Thunderbird main menu.
    • or by selecting &lt;i&gt;Tools&lt;/i&gt; | &lt;i&gt;Add-ons&lt;/i&gt; on the Thunderbird main menu, and then clicking the &lt;i&gt;Options&lt;/i&gt; button.

The first way is recommended, since it allows the coloring/styling changes to be seen while still in the &lt;i&gt;Options&lt;/i&gt; dialog.

&lt;b&gt;Font and Background Colors&lt;/b&gt;

The font and background colors can be set for each account or identity. These colors can be applied to:
    • &lt;i&gt;Account&lt;/i&gt; / &lt;i&gt;Folder&lt;/i&gt; names and &lt;i&gt;Account&lt;/i&gt; / &lt;i&gt;Folder&lt;/i&gt; backgrounds in the folder pane.
    • &lt;i&gt;Subject&lt;/i&gt; / &lt;i&gt;From&lt;/i&gt; names and row backgrounds in the thread pane (message list).
    • &lt;i&gt;Subject&lt;/i&gt; names and message header backgrounds in message pane/tabs/windows and compose windows.
    • &lt;i&gt;From&lt;/i&gt; (and drop-down menu) identities and backgrounds in compose windows.

In the thread pane and message pane/tabs/windows, the colors applied are based either on the account in which the folder containing the message is located, or on the account referenced in the message header. Applying colors based on the account referenced in the message header is especially useful when using a &lt;i&gt;Global Inbox&lt;/i&gt;. 

In compose windows, the colors applied are based on the &lt;i&gt;From&lt;/i&gt; identity. After adding a new identity, the font and background colors must be defined in &lt;i&gt;Options&lt;/i&gt;.

It is possible to retain Thunderbird's default background colors if &lt;i&gt;White&lt;/i&gt; is selected as the background color.

If colors are applied based on the account referenced in the message header, then received messages in IMAP accounts and sent messages in all accounts cannot be colored.

&lt;b&gt;Font Styles and Sizes&lt;/b&gt;

The font style and font size can be changed for:
    • &lt;i&gt;Account&lt;/i&gt; names in the folder pane.
    • &lt;i&gt;Subject&lt;/i&gt; names in the message list.
    • &lt;i&gt;Subject&lt;/i&gt; names in message headers in message pane/tabs/windows.
    • &lt;i&gt;Subject&lt;/i&gt; names and &lt;i&gt;From&lt;/i&gt; identities in message headers in compose windows.

&lt;b&gt;Additional Styles&lt;/b&gt;

Additional styles can be chosen to:
    • bold or underline accounts/folders with new mail in the folder pane.
    • not bold folders with unread messages in the folder pane.
    • only bold the &lt;i&gt;Subject&lt;/i&gt; and/or &lt;i&gt;From&lt;/i&gt; of unread messages in the thread pane.
    • show tree lines in the folder pane.
    • show row stripes in the thread pane.
    • use darker select bars when unfocussed in folder pane and thread pane.
    • increase row spacing with font size in the folder pane and thread pane.

&lt;b&gt;Options&lt;/b&gt;

The &lt;i&gt;Options&lt;/i&gt; dialog box has a tabbed interface. The first tab defines the font and background colors for each account or identity. The subsequent tabs choose whether the font/background colors are to be applied and also choose the font styles/sizes and additional styles to be applied for the folder pane, thread pane, message pane/tabs/windows and compose windows.

&lt;b&gt;Compatibility&lt;/b&gt;

Account Colors is not compatible with the &lt;i&gt;Show InOut&lt;/i&gt; add-on.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">DW-dev</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2014 02:19:05 -0800</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/En-us/thunderbird/addon/account-colors/versions/7.0</guid></item><item><title>Add-ons Manager Context Menu 0.4.2</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/En-us/thunderbird/addon/am-context/</link><description></description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Zulkarnain K.</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 24 Oct 2013 07:20:14 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://addons.mozilla.org/En-us/thunderbird/addon/am-context/versions/0.4.2</guid></item><item><title>Saved Password Editor 2.7.2</title><link>https://addons.mozilla.org/En-us/thunderbird/addon/saved-password-editor/</link><description>This extension allows you to enter data into the Password Manager database instead of relying on Firefox, Thunderbird, SeaMonkey, etc., to do it, as well as making changes to existing entries. For web forms, the typical usage is as follows:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Navigate to the page containing the login form.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Right-click on one of its fields and select from among "Save login info" (to create a new entry), "Edit login info", and "Delete login info".&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If another popup appears, select the username for the entry you want to operate on.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If adding a new entry, everything except the username and password should be filled in automatically. Fill in anything that is missing or incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If adding or editing an entry, reload the page or return later. If the form doesn't get autofilled, most likely the page is asking the browser not to autofill it by declaring autocomplete="off". Try clicking twice on the username field and selecting from the dropdown list. There is &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="http://outgoing.mozilla.org/v1/1183a3c8a4cc37fceb3df4314d7d030f1998f4ba23b9540d